# Integration Test Patterns

Skill for testing game flow, room transitions, events, and end-to-end gameplay in SCPB.

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- Testing complete game flows
- Verifying room transitions work correctly
- Testing event sequences
- End-to-end gameplay testing
- Testing multiple systems together
- Verifying save/load mid-game

## Game Flow Testing

### Full Game Loop Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_FullGameLoop()
    ; Setup fresh game
    StartNewGame()
    SetDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_HARD)

    ; Test: Initial room
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_ENTRANCE_HALL, "Should start in entrance hall")

    ; Test: Collect keycard
    Assert(PlayerHasItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_NONE), "Should have no keycard initially")

    ; Test: Progress through LCZ
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_012)
    PickupItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)
    Assert(PlayerHasItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED), "Should have red keycard")

    ; Test: Enter HCZ
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_GATE_A)
    UseDoor(0)  ; Red door
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_HCZ_002, "Should be in HCZ")

    ; Test: Encounter SCP-173
    Assert(NPCExists(NPC_SCP_173), "SCP-173 should exist")
    Assert(PlayerCanBlink(), "Player should be able to blink")

    ; Test: Die to SCP-173
    MoveIntoRange(NPC_SCP_173)
    DontBlinkFor(10)
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Player should die without blinking")

    ; Test: Game over screen
    Assert(GameOverShown(), "Should show game over")
End Function
```

### Escape Ending Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_EscapeEnding()
    StartNewGame()

    ; Get elevator keycard
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_HCZ_ELEVATOR)
    PickupItem(ITEM_ELEVATOR_KEY)

    ; Go to surface
    UseElevator(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_SURFACE, "Should reach surface")

    ; Find exit
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_SURFACE_GATE)

    ; Test: Sneak past guards
    SetSneaking(True)
    NavigateThroughArea("GUARD_PATROL")
    Assert(NotDetectedByGuards(), "Should sneak past guards")

    ; Escape
    UseDoor(0)
    Assert(GameWon(), "Should win game")

    ; Test: End screen shows
    Assert(EndingScreenShown("ESCAPE"), "Should show escape ending")
End Function
```

## Room Transition Testing

### Door Transition Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_DoorTransitions()
    ; Setup
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_LCZ_012)
    originalRoom = PlayerRoom

    ; Test: Valid door transition
    MovePlayerToDoor(2)  ; Door index 2
    UseDoor(2)
    Assert(PlayerInNewRoom(), "Should transition rooms")
    newRoom = PlayerRoom
    AssertNotEqual(newRoom, originalRoom, "Should be different room")

    ; Test: Door requires keycard
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_LCZ_GATE_A)
    MovePlayerToDoor(0)  ; Red door
    If Not PlayerHasItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)
        Assert(DoorLocked("RED"), "Red door should require red keycard")
        UseDoor(0)
        Assert(PlayerRoom = ROOM_LCZ_GATE_A, "Should not enter locked door")
    End If

    ; Test: Open door with keycard
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)
    UseDoor(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_HCZ_002, "Should enter HCZ")
End Function
```

### Elevator Transition Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_ElevatorTransitions()
    ; Setup
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_LCZ_ELEVATOR_SHAFT)

    ; Test: Call elevator
    CallElevator(0)
    Assert(ElevatorArrived(0), "Elevator should arrive")

    ; Test: Enter elevator
    UseDoor(0)
    Assert(PlayerInElevator(), "Should be in elevator")

    ; Test: Floor selection
    SelectFloor(1)  ; HCZ
    CloseDoor()
    Assert(ElevatorMoving(), "Elevator should move")

    ; Test: Exit at new floor
    AssertEqual(CurrentFloor(), 1, "Should be at HCZ floor")
    OpenDoor()
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_HCZ_ELEVATOR_SHAFT, "Should be in HCZ shaft")

    ; Test: Elevator keycard
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_HCZ_ELEVATOR_SHAFT)
    SelectFloor(2)  ; EZ (requires keycard)
    If Not PlayerHasItem(ITEM_ELEVATOR_KEY)
        Assert(ElevatorRequiresKey("EZ"), "Should require elevator key")
    End If
End Function
```

### Forest Transition Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_ForestTransitions()
    ; Setup
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_FOREST_EDGE)

    ; Test: Enter forest
    MovePlayerToDoor(0)
    UseDoor(0)
    Assert(PlayerInForest(), "Should be in forest")

    ; Test: Forest navigation
    NavigateForest("PATH_NORTH")
    Assert(AtForestLocation("CABIN"), "Should reach cabin")

    ; Test: Forest dangers
    SetPlayerPosition(ForestDangerZone())
    Assert(PlayerTakingDamage("THORNS"), "Should take damage in thorns")

    ; Test: Exit forest
    NavigateForest("PATH_SOUTH")
    MovePlayerToExit()
    UseDoor(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_ENTRANCE_HALL, "Should exit forest")
End Function
```

## Event Sequence Testing

### SCP-173 Encounter Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP173_EncounterSequence()
    StartNewGame()
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_173)

    ; Test: First sighting
    Assert(PlayerSeesNPC(NPC_SCP_173), "Should see SCP-173")
    Assert(SCPActive(NPC_SCP_173), "SCP-173 should be active")

    ; Test: Blink system active
    Assert(BlinkSystemEnabled(), "Blink system should be enabled")

    ; Test: Observation freezes SCP
    LookAtNPC(NPC_SCP_173)
    UpdateNPCs()
    prevPos = GetNPCPosition(NPC_SCP_173)
    WaitFrames(10)
    currPos = GetNPCPosition(NPC_SCP_173)
    AssertEqual(prevPos, currPos, "SCP-173 should freeze when observed")

    ; Test: Look away triggers movement
    LookAway()
    UpdateNPCs()
    WaitFrames(60)
    currPos = GetNPCPosition(NPC_SCP_173)
    AssertNotEqual(prevPos, currPos, "SCP-173 should move when not observed")

    ; Test: Proximity snap
    SetPlayerPositionNearNPC(NPC_SCP_173, 3.0)
    LookAway()
    WaitFrames(10)
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Player should die at close range without blinking")
End Function
```

### SCP-096 Encounter Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP096_EncounterSequence()
    StartNewGame()
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_HCZ_096)

    ; Test: Find note about not looking
    ReadSign("WARNING_096")
    Assert(PlayerKnowsNotToLook(), "Player should know not to look")

    ; Test: Peek without full view
    PeekAtDoor(ROOM_HCZ_096)
    AssertNotEqual(SCPActive(NPC_SCP_096), True, "SCP-096 should not trigger from peek")

    ; Test: Accidental view triggers pursuit
    MoveThroughDoor(0)
    fullView = PlayerSeesNPCFullView(NPC_SCP_096)
    Assert(fullView, "Player sees full view")
    Assert(SCPActive(NPC_SCP_096), "SCP-096 should activate")

    ; Test: Cannot escape once triggered
    RunAway()
    Assert(SCPPursuing(NPC_SCP_096), "SCP-096 should pursue")

    ; Test: Death when caught
    WaitForNPCToCatchPlayer()
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Player should die when SCP-096 catches")
End Function
```

### MTF Ambush Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_MTFAmbush()
    StartNewGame()

    ; Test: No MTF initially
    AssertEqual(CountNPCsOfType(NPC_MTF), 0, "No MTF at start")

    ; Advance to 6 minutes
    AdvanceTime(360)

    ; Test: MTF spawn
    Assert(CountNPCsOfType(NPC_MTF) > 0, "MTF should spawn at 6 minutes")

    ; Test: MTF hostile
    npc = GetFirstNPCOfType(NPC_MTF)
    Assert(MTFTargetsPlayer(npc), "MTF should target player")

    ; Test: Combat
    PlayerShootNPC(npc)
    Assert(NPCTakingDamage(npc), "MTF should take damage")

    ; Test: MTF can kill player
    PlayerHealth = 100
    MTFAttackPlayer(npc)
    Assert(PlayerHealth < 100, "MTF should damage player")
End Function
```

## Save/Load Integration Test

### Mid-Game Save Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_MidGameSave()
    StartNewGame()
    SetDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_HARD)

    ; Progress game
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_012)
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)
    KillNPC(NPC_SCP_173)

    ; Record state
    savedHealth = PlayerHealth
    savedRoom = PlayerRoom
    savedItems = GetInventory()
    savedNPCs = GetDeadNPCs()

    ; Save game
    SaveGame(0)

    ; Test: Load restores exact state
    LoadGame(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerHealth(), savedHealth, "Health should match")
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), savedRoom, "Room should match")
    AssertEqual(GetInventory(), savedItems, "Items should match")
    AssertEqual(GetDeadNPCs(), savedNPCs, "Dead NPCs should match")

    ; Test: Can continue playing
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_914)
    Assert(CanContinuePlaying(), "Game should continue normally")
End Function
```

### Death and Load Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_DeathAndLoad()
    StartNewGame()

    ; Die
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_173)
    MoveIntoRange(NPC_SCP_173)
    DontBlinkFor(15)
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Player should die")

    ; Test: Death screen
    Assert(DeathScreenShown(), "Should show death screen")

    ; Test: Can load save
    SelectLoadSlot(0)
    LoadGame(0)
    Assert(PlayerAlive(), "Player should be alive after loading")

    ; Test: Back at pre-death state
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_LCZ_173, "Should be back at SCP room")
    Assert(NPCAlive(NPC_SCP_173), "SCP-173 should be alive")
End Function
```

## Inventory Integration Test

### Full Inventory Flow Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_InventoryFlow()
    StartNewGame()

    ; Test: Start with no items
    AssertEqual(CountInventoryItems(), 0, "Empty inventory at start")

    ; Test: Pickup items
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_LCZ_012)
    PickupItem(ITEM_MEDKIT)
    AssertEqual(CountInventoryItems(), 1, "Should have 1 item")

    ; Test: Use medkit
    PlayerHealth = 50
    SelectItem(ITEM_MEDKIT)
    UseItem()
    Assert(PlayerHealth > 50, "Health should increase")
    AssertEqual(CountInventoryItems(), 0, "Medkit should be used")

    ; Test: Combine items
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_BATTERY)
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_FLASHLIGHT)
    SelectItem(ITEM_BATTERY)
    CombineWith(ITEM_FLASHLIGHT)
    Assert(PlayerHasItem(ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT), "Should have working flashlight")

    ; Test: Drag and drop
    MoveItemInInventory(0, 2)
    Assert(ItemAtSlot(2) == ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT, "Item should move")

    ; Test: Save with items
    savedItems = GetInventory()
    SaveGame(0)
    LoadGame(0)
    AssertEqual(GetInventory(), savedItems, "Items should persist")
End Function
```

## Performance Integration Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_PerformanceUnderLoad()
    StartNewGame()

    ; Test: FPS in empty room
    StartFPSMeasurement()
    NavigateToRoom(ROOM_ENTRANCE_HALL)
    WaitFrames(60)
    emptyRoomFPS = GetAverageFPS()
    Assert(emptyRoomFPS > 30, "Should have good FPS in empty room")

    ; Test: FPS with many NPCs
    SpawnNPCs(10)
    StartFPSMeasurement()
    WaitFrames(60)
    crowdedFPS = GetAverageFPS()
    Assert(crowdedFPS > 20, "Should maintain playable FPS with NPCs")

    ; Test: FPS in forest
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_FOREST_DEEP)
    StartFPSMeasurement()
    WaitFrames(60)
    forestFPS = GetAverageFPS()
    Assert(forestFPS > 20, "Should have playable FPS in forest")

    ; Report
    Print "Performance Results:"
    Print "Empty room: " + emptyRoomFPS + " FPS"
    Print "With NPCs: " + crowdedFPS + " FPS"
    Print "Forest: " + forestFPS + " FPS"
End Function
```

## Test Runner

```blitzbasic
Global INTEGRATION_TEST_PASSED%
Global INTEGRATION_TEST_FAILED%

Function RunIntegrationTests()
    INTEGRATION_TEST_PASSED = 0
    INTEGRATION_TEST_FAILED = 0

    Print "Running Integration Tests..."
    Print "================================"

    ; Game flow tests
    Print "Game Flow Tests:"
    RunTest("FullGameLoop", Test_FullGameLoop)
    RunTest("EscapeEnding", Test_EscapeEnding)

    ; Room transition tests
    Print "Room Transition Tests:"
    RunTest("DoorTransitions", Test_DoorTransitions)
    RunTest("ElevatorTransitions", Test_ElevatorTransitions)
    RunTest("ForestTransitions", Test_ForestTransitions)

    ; Event sequence tests
    Print "Event Sequence Tests:"
    RunTest("SCP173Encounter", Test_SCP173_EncounterSequence)
    RunTest("SCP096Encounter", Test_SCP096_EncounterSequence)
    RunTest("MTFAmbush", Test_MTFAmbush)

    ; Save/load tests
    Print "Save/Load Tests:"
    RunTest("MidGameSave", Test_MidGameSave)
    RunTest("DeathAndLoad", Test_DeathAndLoad)

    ; Inventory tests
    Print "Inventory Tests:"
    RunTest("InventoryFlow", Test_InventoryFlow)

    ; Performance tests
    Print "Performance Tests:"
    RunTest("PerformanceUnderLoad", Test_PerformanceUnderLoad)

    Print "================================"
    Print "Integration Tests: " + INTEGRATION_TEST_PASSED + " passed, " + INTEGRATION_TEST_FAILED + " failed"

    Return INTEGRATION_TEST_FAILED = 0
End Function

Function RunTest(name$, testFunc)
    Print "  Running " + name$ + "..."
    Excute testFunc
    If GetLastAssertFailed()
        Print "    FAILED: " + GetLastAssertMessage()
        INTEGRATION_TEST_FAILED = INTEGRATION_TEST_FAILED + 1
    Else
        Print "    PASSED"
        INTEGRATION_TEST_PASSED = INTEGRATION_TEST_PASSED + 1
    End If
End Function
```

## Quick Reference

| Test Category | Key Tests |
|--------------|-----------|
| Game Flow | Start to death, escape ending |
| Transitions | Doors, elevators, forest |
| Events | SCP encounters, MTF ambush |
| Save/Load | Mid-game save, death and load |
| Inventory | Full flow, combine, drag-drop |
| Performance | FPS under load |
